org).

 The further hypothesis is that despite CMR detectable infarction the incidence of clinical type IV MI will be low.

 CMR scans will be performed 1 week before, 1 week and 6 months post rotablation.

 Cardiac troponin and ECGs will be performed post rotablation to determine the incidence of type IV MI.

